# Implementation Plan - Google OAuth 2.0 & Online Status Tracking

Upgrading account security with a production-ready Google OAuth flow and introducing real-time online status monitoring for the staff roster.

## User Review Required

> [!IMPORTANT]
> **Google OAuth Configuration**:
> We will add a real Google OAuth authorization callback on the backend (`GET /api/auth/google/callback`). 
> * If `GOOGLE_CLIENT_ID` and `GOOGLE_CLIENT_SECRET` are set in your `.env`, clicking Google login will redirect to the Google Consent screen, verify your identity, and log you in.
> * If they are not set, it will gracefully run in the **Developer Sandbox Simulation** window as before.

> [!TIP]
> **Online vs Active Status**:
> We will distinguish between two fields:
> 1. **Active/Suspended Status**: Managed by the owner to deactivate/activate staff accounts (saved in `isActive`).
> 2. **Online/Offline Status**: Computed dynamically based on the user's last API request timestamp (`lastActiveAt`). If the user made any request within the last 5 minutes, they will show as **Online** with a green pulse dot in the staff roster.

