### Backend Layer

#### [MODIFY] [auth.js (middleware)](file:///c:/Users/justi/Downloads/School%20Files/MainProjectCollection/ComprogStudies/ProjectsWebDev/Capstone Things/DeveloperVersion/backend/middleware/auth.js)
- Inside `authenticateUser`, update the user's `lastActiveAt` to `new Date()` asynchronously on every authenticated request.

#### [MODIFY] [authController.js](file:///c:/Users/justi/Downloads/School%20Files/MainProjectCollection/ComprogStudies/ProjectsWebDev/Capstone Things/DeveloperVersion/backend/controllers/authController.js)
- **`getGoogleConfig`**: Returns whether Google OAuth is configured (`isConfigured`) and the client ID (`clientId`).
- **`googleCallback`**: 
  - Exposes `GET /api/auth/google/callback`.
  - Exchanges the Google OAuth redirection `code` for an access token by calling `https://oauth2.googleapis.com/token`.
  - Retrieves Google user info (`email`, `id`) from `https://www.googleapis.com/oauth2/v3/userinfo`.
  - Searches database for matching `googleEmail`, `googleId`, or primary `email`.
  - Logs them in (issues cookie JWT) and redirects to homepage, or redirects with error message `?error=google_not_linked` if no account is associated.
- **`getStaff`**: Update roster list retrieval to include `lastActiveAt` in the response so the owner can view online status.

#### [MODIFY] [authRoutes.js](file:///c:/Users/justi/Downloads/School%20Files/MainProjectCollection/ComprogStudies/ProjectsWebDev/Capstone Things/DeveloperVersion/backend/routes/authRoutes.js)
- Expose GET `/api/auth/google/config`
- Expose GET `/api/auth/google/callback`

